questionRound.0.question.9.answer: I clicked on the payoffs of the color I was dependent on for my own and sometimes even the payoffs of the color in the payoff box of my color to try to guess their reasoning and motivations and consequently which they would pick. Sometimes I was right  and sometimes I was wrong. Most often I was wrong when I didn't check the payoffs of most if not all everyone involved. No one really seemed to be going for a mutually beneficial payoff  it was mostly selfishly desired--people would go for their own higher payoff at the detriment of others.
Other groups would choose based on what got them the most points and so you would work off that but it didn't always work out well

I compare the different amount of money based on the other player's decision  and choose the one that will yield the highest outcome.

questionRound.0.question.9.answer: first i would look at the other other colors box that played a part in the amout of tokens i would win.  i would look at the color that played a part in their choice and see what i would think that third color would choose. after determining that i would determine what i think the second color would choose so i could look at my own box and based off of my prediction on the second color  make the choice on which number would most likely give me the greater profit. a majority of the time it worked in my favor.

I looked "2 back" from my own position: that is  I looked at the payoff of the person not who I was dependent on  but with the person they were dependent on. Based on what that person's "best" choice would be  I chose my own answer. I also noticed that this generally meant choosing the row with the second-highest number in it.
Looked at the payoff of the color my outcome depended on. Always assumed that they would chose the largest given value and played my game accordingly.

questionRound.0.question.9.answer: I would try and guess what my opponents move would be  by trying to predict his opponents move. I would then make my move to maximize my benefit after this prediction was made.

I realized that I had to consider what my match partner would pick rather than solely look at my options. And to determine what he would pick  I would look at his match's payouts to determine what his match partner would pick  until it came to a point where a match competitor had a dominant strategy. In the case of a dominant strategy  I knew a player would pick a particular row no matter what. Based on that  a player would pick a row  and it would keep going until it got to me. However  this technique was depending on hoping that other players would use the same technique.

I looked at the other choices of the other player that affected my payoff and tried to determine which option they would choose. Based on that I chose the best option that would get me the most money. Of course if there was a row in which both numbers were higher than the numbers in the other row than I chose the higher payoff row.
